# The pitch

.alt[Backslide] is a CLI tool for making HTML presentations with [Remark.js](https://github.com/gnab/remark) using [Markdown](https://github.com/adam-p/markdown-here/wiki/Markdown-Cheatsheet)

### Features

- Template generator with [Sass](http://sass-lang.com) styling
- Live preview server
- Self-contained HTML export
- Automated PDF conversion
- Multiple presentations support

???

- Show presenter mode with `p`
- Blackout works too! (press `b` ;-)

---

# Getting started

## Installation

- **Prerequisites**: [NodeJS](https://nodejs.org) v7.6+

```sh
# create project directory
$ mkdir my-presentation && cd my-presentation
# install globally with NPM
$ npm install -g backslide
# or Yarn
$ yarn global add backslide
$ bs init
$ bs serve
```

Open `presentation.md` with your favorite [editor](https://code.visualstudio.com) and start making changes!

# Export options

## HTML

Use `bs export` to export your presentations as self-contained HTML.

> **Pro tip:** If you use images, include them as [data-uri](https://css-tricks.com/data-uris/) in your markdown so your HTML can be completely viewed offline

## PDF

Use `bs pdf` to export your presentations as PDF.

> This feature use [Decktape](https://github.com/astefanutti/decktape).
